annotationA: Sugarlethal, isoform A; Sugarlethal encodes pyridoxine 5'-phosphate oxidase (PNPO). PNPO converts pyridoxine to its active form pyridoxal 5'-phosphate (PLP). PLP is a co-factor required for more than 100 enzymes that function in amino acid metabolism, gluconeogenesis and neurotransmitter synthesis
annotationB: Pyridoxal kinase is the enzyme that generates Pyridoxal-5-phosphate, the metabolically active form of vitamin B6. It contributes to chromosome integrity and glucose homeostasis
